reviews.text:
Pretty, old-fashioned train station. The cast-iron roof is split in two arched sections, and the platforms are curved, making for a very nice view.
Not a particularly large or otherwise remarkable station, but bright and friendly.
Clean. Helpful staff running smoothly for once 🤪 very quiet for a holiday (kids) Sunday

The only problem I have with Brighton Chippy is when choosing the Plaice and chips option. They obviously have times when they sell too few portions of Plaice. It is often not as fresh as Cod etc. The chef did warn me of this but I thought it can't be that bad as the Cod is so good-they should bin the fish if it is not really fresh.

Pete.

It's a very diverse city.Probably one of the least britush one in uk(if you think.of Britishness as having mainly conservative and traditional traits).Lots of great quirky shops,amasing art.The beach has pebbles though:)
It has good location, is well organised and has kind and very helpfull staff from the Southern Railway.
